1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,140
We sold a product that didn't exist.

2
00:00:03,300 --> 00:00:06,920
Watch a cashier scans something brand new, names it,

3
00:00:07,640 --> 00:00:10,320
prices it, snaps a photo, sells it,

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,380
The receipt prints. The points land.

5
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:18,560
the customer walks out happy. Everything looks perfect.

6
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:22,200
Two minutes later she goes to ring up another one.

7
00:00:23,120 --> 00:00:27,040
She searches the name. Nothing, no matches.

8
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:30,940
The product she just made and sold is gone.

9
00:00:31,660 --> 00:00:35,620
The sale was real, the money was real, the points were real,

10
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:38,960
but the product never saved, never in the catalog.

11
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:42,900
It vanished the second the receipt printed. A phantom.

12
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:49,980
Now imagine that's your shop. Every new barcode a cashier scans sold once

13
00:00:49,980 --> 00:00:54,000
then gone. A catalog full of holes. The one

14
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,620
promised this whole thing makes scan once,

15
00:00:57,520 --> 00:01:01,220
known forever, silently broken, and nobody notices

16
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:04,400
because the sale never fails.

17
00:01:05,740 --> 00:01:08,500
So we hunted it. There are two ways to make a product.

18
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:11,340
One, let the cashier straight through. It's twin.

19
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:16,480
The one that fires when you scan a fresh barcode, slam the door.

20
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:20,720
A permission error, swallowed in silence. One seal worked.

21
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:22,840
The identical seal right next to it

22
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:28,820
leaked. We found it. One line. We sent the barcode through

23
00:01:28,820 --> 00:01:31,800
the same door. The cashier was already allowed through.

24
00:01:32,940 --> 00:01:36,260
And now she scans, creates, sells, searches.

25
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:42,420
There it is. It's stuck forever. Found on a phone,

26
00:01:42,620 --> 00:01:46,400
killed before ever touched a real shop because if one seal fails,

27
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:51,460
you check all the seals. That's the difference between software that's

28
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:55,020
tested and the software that has been lived in.
